{"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/neptune\/secp256k1\/init(seed:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Neptune\/documentation\/Neptune","doc:\/\/Neptune\/documentation\/Neptune\/SECP256K1"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"seed"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5UInt8V","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UInt8"},{"kind":"text","text":"]? = nil) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional 32-byte random seed for context randomization. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a cryptographically secure random seed will be generated automatically. If provided,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"must be exactly 32 bytes in length."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"seed"}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The context is an opaque data structure that stores:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Randomization data"}]},{"text":" (primary purpose): Blinding values used for side-channel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"protection during elliptic curve operations involving secret keys","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Precomputation tables"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Optimized lookup tables for elliptic curve point","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"multiplications with the generator point (G)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Error callbacks","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Function pointers for handling illegal arguments and errors","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What randomization does:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Randomization uses a 32-byte seed to generate secret blinding values that mask"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"internal computations. This makes operations like signing and public key generation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"resistant to side-channel attacks (power analysis, timing attacks, electromagnetic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"leakage) by ensuring that the internal computation patterns are independent of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"secret key values. Specifically, the seed is used to blind scalar multiplications"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the base point, transforming operations like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"R = gn*G"},{"type":"text","text":" into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"R = (gn - b)*G + b*G"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"type":"text","text":" is a secret random blinding value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-threading:"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A constructed context can safely be used from multiple threads simultaneously for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"read-only operations. However, operations that modify the context (like randomization","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or destruction) require exclusive access. Since this initializer randomizes the context","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at creation time, no additional locking is needed for subsequent read-only operations","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"across threads. If you need to re-randomize the context later, use appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"synchronization (e.g., a read-write lock) to coordinate access.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Throws","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SECPError.randomGenerationFailed if secure random bytes cannot be generated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or if the provided seed is not exactly 32 bytes"}]}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Throws","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SECPError.contextRandomizationFailed if context randomization fails"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"init","externalID":"s:7Neptune9SECP256K1C4seedACSays5UInt8VGSg_tKcfc","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"seed","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": [","kind":"text"},{"text":"UInt8","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5UInt8V"},{"text":"]?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"}],"modules":[{"name":"Neptune"}],"role":"symbol","title":"init(seed:)","roleHeading":"Initializer"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Neptune\/documentation\/Neptune\/SECP256K1\/init(seed:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates and randomizes a new SECP256K1 context","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://Neptune/documentation/Neptune":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"collection","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/neptune","title":"Neptune","identifier":"doc:\/\/Neptune\/documentation\/Neptune"},"doc://Neptune/documentation/Neptune/SECP256K1/init(seed:)":{"title":"init(seed:)","abstract":[{"text":"Creates and randomizes a new SECP256K1 context","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/neptune\/secp256k1\/init(seed:)","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"seed"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5UInt8V","text":"UInt8"},{"kind":"text","text":"]?) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Neptune\/documentation\/Neptune\/SECP256K1\/init(seed:)"},"doc://Neptune/documentation/Neptune/SECP256K1":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SECP256K1","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A class for performing SECP256K1 elliptic curve operations","type":"text"}],"title":"SECP256K1","url":"\/documentation\/neptune\/secp256k1","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SECP256K1","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Neptune\/documentation\/Neptune\/SECP256K1"}}}